# ============================================================================
# Wave 27 — context-ranking: bigram evidence at ranking/margin time
# ============================================================================
# The class (session-analyzer top-gaps table): the intended word is generated
# but outranked or under-margined in contexts where the previous word's
# bigram should decide it. Mechanisms: (1) fold-twin bigram context backoff
# (an unattested previous word reads bigrams through its dominant acute-fold
# twin — "eg" contexts ARE "ég" contexts); (2) bigram-dominance margin
# relief (winner with strong contextual lift over a lift-less runner-up
# clears a reduced margin); (3) context-backed 3-char discipline (an
# error-class rewrite of a 3-letter token needs a headline winner unless
# the bigram with the previous word vouches for it); (4) bigram-continuation
# proposals for 3-4 char tokens (context proposes followers, the typed keys
# verify — the only path to a word outside every short edit budget).

SCENARIO cold-start eg gret restores grét (2026-07-16T22-45-30, wave 27)
# No personal seeds (wave 26 covered the seeded case): grét leads on the
# "ég grét" bigram (222, lift +1.26σ) but sat 0.469 nats over the
# morph-boosted completion "greta" against the 0.5 restoration margin.
# Bigram-dominance relief (winner lift +1.26, runner-up bigram-less)
# drops the bar to 0.35 — grét fires.
T "son minn eg gret "
EXPECT_LAST_COMMIT grét

